# Project stack — this repository

This repo is **Cursor Collections** (Eversis): **Cursor** rules, attachable prompts under **`.cursor/prompts/`** (synced into `website/docs/prompts/` for the docs site), skills in **`.github/skills/`**, and [documentation/cursor-collection.md](documentation/cursor-collection.md).

| Area | This repository |
| ---- | --------------- |
| **Product** | Cursor-native product engineering framework + published workflow docs |
| **Docs site** | Docusaurus 3 under **`website/`** (`cursor-collections-docs`) |
| **Prompts** | **`.cursor/prompts/public/`** and **`internal/`** (`eversis-*.md`); attach with **`@eversis-*`**; **`sync-prompts`** copies to gitignored `website/docs/prompts/` (also in **`.cursorignore`** to avoid double **`@`** indexing) |
| **Skills** | **`.github/skills/eversis-*/`** (topic packages; list/read/validate via **`eversis-collections` MCP**, not a separate **Agent Skills** path) |

## Quality commands (this repo)

Run from **`website/`** (see [website/package.json](website/package.json)):

- **Dev server:** `npm start` (Docusaurus)
- **Production build:** `npm run build` — use this as the primary quality gate for doc changes
- **Serve build locally:** `npm run serve`

There is no root `lint` / `test` script; the site is mostly Markdown and React theme.

## Conventions

- Feature specs for *downstream* or experimental work: **`docs/specs/*.spec.md`**
- Internal notes: **`docs/context/*.md`**
- **Template** for other projects: see **“Reference: Eversis stack example”** in [documentation/cursor-collection.md](../../documentation/cursor-collection.md)
